@alnevillegas5183

3 years ago (edited)
The line “I’ll save you a seat // hang my coat on a chair next to me” is so subtle but such incredibly imagery. I love that this song is singing about a future lover. You don’t get many songs now a days about anticipating love in a way that is so hopeful. Bruno daydreaming in the end supports the fact that love really is in the stars— it’s so random and you could miss it at any chance, but then things end up aligning in situations. For instance, look at a current or past lover— would that love have happened if you weren't at a certain location or event, or did a certain thing? Probably not. This has got to be one of the most beautifully written songs out there. Simply put so eloquently. Thank you Bruno and Finneas for this gem. A killer duo!
